- The query appears to contain an error in the join condition with `TopReviewer`, which will prevent it from returning any rows for the top reviewer and their progress; 
- Average rating is calculated based on the 'mark' given by users, which is likely a subjective rating system;
- The total number of pages read is calculated for each user based on their progress in reading books.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT book_id) 
FROM user_book_progress 
WHERE pages_read > 3;

SELECT genre_id, MAX(mark) AS highest_rating
FROM books
GROUP BY genre_id;

SELECT DISTINCT b.title
FROM books b
WHERE b.book_id IN (
  SELECT a.book_id
  FROM awards a
);
